  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/botany/terms/chenopodium-capitatum/> ;
  schema:name "Chenopodium capitatum" ;
  schema:description "Hardy annual or short-lived perennial from Amaranthaceae, native to western North America. Produces spinach-like leaves in juvenile phase; bolts to produce dense fruiting spikes bearing small red berries. Dual-harvest crop: early leaves, then post-bolting berries. Self-seeds aggressively; hardy to USDA zone 2." ;
